<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 07 at 6:23PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Fergus
County through 700 PM MDT...
At 623 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 21
miles southwest of Fourchette, or 25 miles south of Zortman, moving
east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern Fergus
County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
